- Known follow-ups recorded in DESIGN.md:
 1. Tile size inflation (15GB for 582 Swedish charts) — tile boundary clipping would reduce this 4–6× by keeping coordinates within tile extent for better varint compression
 2. Peak 22GB RSS — can be reduced by streaming tiles to disk instead of buffering all in a BTreeMap
 3. Multi-zoom bands — each chart currently serves only at its exact native zoom; MapLibre overzooms for intermediate levels


 - Problem 1 — z<8 white
 Root cause: no tiles exist below z=8 because the coarsest charts are 1:1.5M → z=8.
 MapLibre requests z=7 tiles, gets 204, shows white. My change has no effect here.
 Fix: lower MIN_ZOOM from 8 to e.g. 4. The same downward-fill loop already handles it —
 the coarsest charts just also write at z=4-7.

 Problem 2 — z=9-11 sporadic white (what you asked about)
 Root cause: an area covered only by a fine-scale chart (native z=12-14) had no tiles
 at z=9-11. MapLibre doesn't fall back to a coarser tile automatically within the
 min/max range.
 Fix: this is what I implemented — for zoom in MIN_ZOOM..=native_zoom so every chart
 also writes at all zoom levels from z=8 down to its native zoom. A z=14 chart now
 fills z=8-14, eliminating the gaps.

 Problem 3 — z=16+ mostly white
 Root cause: opposite direction. The finest chart in an area might be z=14; at viewport
 z=16 MapLibre requests z=16 tiles, gets 204. My fix only extends downward from native
 zoom, not upward.
 Two options:
 - Extend upward in tile generation — expensive: ×4 tiles per extra zoom level added
 above native zoom
 - Set maxzoom lower in the style/source config — MapLibre then overzooms (stretches)
 the finest available tile for all viewport zooms above it, no white. One-line change
 in style.json. Tradeoff: harbour charts at z=18 show z=maxzoom tiles at viewport z=18
 instead of z=18 tiles

 So: problem 2 is done. Problems 1 and 3 need separate fixes — do you want both, and
